Note about the tracks:
All -san and -kuns are intact in both versions. 
In the Non-Otaku version Shinigami is translated out as god of death and Onii-chan is translated out as Big brother. That's the only difference in the scripts. Thought about calling it the Weeaboo translation for the concept of using Japanese when a perfectly good English equivalent exists, but decided a true to form Weeaboo would likewise use the Japanese term Otaku instead of the English Weeaboo too. 

Your translator strongly prefers Otaku style translations on everything, though the references to gods and God probably works better in English when Shinigami's also translated out as god of death. But those familiar with the term Shinigami probably make those connections without needing them spelled out so blatantly
